    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, there are ways to ensure his assets are protected, but it depends heavily on whether the chosen agent is trustworthy and capable of handling the situation. If your dad picks a reliable agent and the Durable Power of Attorney is properly executed, that person has the legal authority to step in immediately upon incapacity, preventing his assets from being frozen or mismanaged. For extra protection, you can add specific instructions in the document, like naming a backup agent (a \"successor\") who takes over if the first person is unavailable or unable to serve. Additionally, consulting with a probate attorney to review the entire plan can help identify potential risks and ensure the document is drafted correctly to withstand legal challenges. It's also wise to keep a copy of the signed document in a safe place with your dad and share it with the agent so they can access it quickly when needed.",
      "source": "target",
